.head 3 +  Function: NewChangeLogic
.head 4 -  Description: To handle the logic required when changing a customer order
This function used the nLess20OkDontAsk and nLess20NotOkDontAsk flags so be carefull
when changing code.
.head 4 +  Returns
.head 5 -  Boolean:
.head 4 +  Parameters
.head 5 -  Number: nCustNo
.head 5 -  Date/Time: dtOrderSysDT
.head 5 -  Number: nItemNo
.head 5 -  Number: nYear
.head 5 -  Number: nOrdAmt
.head 5 -  Number: nConfAmt
.head 5 -  String: sAllocFlag
.head 5 -  String: sSubsOkFlag
.head 5 -  Number: nBatchLocId
.head 5 -  Number: nBatchYear
.head 5 -  Receive Number: nNewSubItemNo
.head 5 -  Receive Number: nOldYear
.head 5 -  Receive Boolean: bLogicChange
.head 5 -  Number: nActionType
.head 4 -  Static Variables
.head 4 +  Local variables
.head 5 -  String: sGenericFlag
.head 5 -  String: sOldGenericFlag
.head 5 -  Boolean: bOk
.head 5 -  Boolean: bCheckItem
.head 5 -  !
.head 5 -  Number: nOldItemNo
.head 5 -  Number: nOldSubsItemNo
.head 5 -  ! Number: nOldYear
.head 5 -  Number: nOldOrdAmt
.head 5 -  Number: nOldConfAmt
.head 5 -  String: sOldAllocFlag
.head 5 -  Number: nOldBatchLocId
.head 5 -  Number: nOldBatchYear
.head 5 -  !
.head 5 -  ! Number: nPassDownActionType
.head 4 +  Actions
.head 5 +  If IsFlagSet( nActionType, SH_cls_Execute )
.head 6 -  Set bLogicChange = FALSE
.head 6 -  Set nNewSubItemNo = NUMBER_Null
.head 6 +  If GetOrderBasicDetails( nCustNo, dtOrderSysDT, nOldItemNo, nOldSubsItemNo, nOldYear, nOldOrdAmt, nOldConfAmt, sOldAllocFlag, nOldBatchLocId, nOldBatchYear, SH_cls_Execute )
.head 7 +  If nOldYear = nYear
.head 8 +  If nOldItemNo = nItemNo
.head 9 +  If nOldOrdAmt = nOrdAmt
.head 10 +  If sOldAllocFlag = sAllocFlag
.head 11 +  If nOldConfAmt = nConfAmt
.head 12 +  If nOldBatchLocId = nBatchLocId
.head 13 +  If nOldBatchYear = nBatchYear
.head 14 -  ! Then nothing has changed to the 5 fields that impact the total amount on order
so we dont need to update anything
.head 14 -  Return TRUE
.head 7 -  ! Dani added to stop users increasing an ordered amount
.head 7 -  ! Jan took out the check for increasing or decreasing conf_amount
  this should be done local to the screen
.head 7 +  If nOldConfAmt = NUMBER_Null
.head 8 +  If nOldOrdAmt < nOrdAmt
.head 9 -  Call SalMessageBeep( 0 )
.head 9 +  If NOT SalSendMsg( hWndForm, PAM_ORDERMSGNOTIFY, ORDER_Save, ORDERMSG_IncreaseOrdAmt )
.head 10 -  Call SalMessageBox( 'You cannot increase an ordered amount', 'Order', MB_Ok )
.head 9 -  Return FALSE
.head 7 +  If nConfAmt < 0 AND NOT nConfAmt  = NUMBER_Null
.head 8 -  Call SalMessageBeep( 0 )
.head 8 +  If NOT SalSendMsg( hWndForm, PAM_ORDERMSGNOTIFY, ORDER_Save, ORDERMSG_DecreaseConfB0 )
.head 9 -  Call SalMessageBox( 'You cannot decrease a confirmed amount below zero!', 'Order', MB_Ok )
.head 8 -  Return FALSE
.head 7 -  !
.head 7 +  If NOT nOldItemNo = nItemNo
.head 8 -  Set bCheckItem = FALSE
.head 8 +  If NOT nConfAmt = NUMBER_Null
.head 9 +  If nConfAmt > 0
.head 10 -  Set bCheckItem = TRUE
.head 8 +  Else If nOrdAmt > 0
.head 9 -  Set bCheckItem = TRUE
.head 8 -  !
.head 8 +  If bCheckItem
.head 9 +  If IsFlagSet( nActionType, nItemCheck )
.head 10 +  If CheckItemIsOkForCust( nItemNo, nYear, nCustNo, bOk, nActionType )
.head 11 +  If NOT bOk
.head 12 -  Call SalMessageBeep( 0 )
.head 12 -  Return FALSE
.head 7 -  !
.head 7 -  Set bLogicChange = TRUE
.head 7 +  If GetGenericStockItemFlag( nItemNo, sGenericFlag, SH_cls_Execute )
.head 8 +  If GetGenericStockItemFlag( nOldItemNo, sOldGenericFlag, SH_cls_Execute )
.head 9 +  If NewDeductFromStockItemSale( nOldItemNo, nOldYear, nOldOrdAmt, nOldConfAmt, sOldAllocFlag, sOldGenericFlag, nOldBatchLocId, nOldBatchYear,  SH_cls_Execute  )
.head 10 +  If nOldSubsItemNo > 0
.head 11 +  If NOT NewDeleteFromSub( nOldSubsItemNo, nOldYear, nOldOrdAmt, nOldConfAmt, sOldAllocFlag, SH_cls_Execute )
.head 12 -  Return FALSE
.head 10 -  !
.head 10 +  ! If IsFlagSet( nActionType, nLess20OkDontAsk )
.head 11 -  Set nPassDownActionType = SH_cls_Execute | nLess20OkDontAsk
.head 10 +  ! Else If IsFlagSet( nActionType, nLess20NotOkDontAsk )
.head 11 -  Set nPassDownActionType = SH_cls_Execute | nLess20OkDontAsk
.head 10 +  ! Else
.head 11 -  Set nPassDownActionType = SH_cls_Execute
.head 10 +  If NewAddToStockItemSale( nItemNo, nYear, nOrdAmt, nConfAmt, sAllocFlag, sGenericFlag, sSubsOkFlag, nBatchLocId, nBatchYear, nNewSubItemNo, nActionType )
.head 11 -  Return TRUE
.head 10 +  Else
.head 11 -  Return FALSE
.head 9 +  Else
.head 10 -  Return FALSE
.head 8 +  Else
.head 9 -  Return FALSE
.head 7 +  Else
.head 8 -  Return FALSE
.head 6 +  Else
.head 7 -  Return FALSE
.head 5 +  Else If IsFlagSet( nActionType, SH_cls_Commit )
.head 6 -  Set bOk = TRUE
.head 6 +  If NOT NewDeductFromStockItemSale( 0, 0, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 0, SH_cls_Commit  )
.head 7 -  Set bOk = FALSE
.head 6 +  If NOT NewAddToStockItemSale( 0, 0, 0, 0, '', '', '', 0, 0, nNewSubItemNo, SH_cls_Commit )
.head 7 -  Set bOk = FALSE
.head 6 +  If NOT NewDeleteFromSub( 0, 0, 0, 0, '', SH_cls_Commit )
.head 7 -  Set bOk = FALSE
.head 6 +  If NOT CheckItemIsOkForCust( 0, 0, 0, bOk, SH_cls_Commit )
.head 7 -  Set bOk = FALSE
.head 6 -  Return bOk
.head 5 +  Else If IsFlagSet( nActionType, SH_cls_Rollback )
.head 6 -  Set bOk = TRUE
.head 6 +  If NOT NewDeductFromStockItemSale( 0, 0, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 0, SH_cls_Rollback  )
.head 7 -  Set bOk = FALSE
.head 6 +  If NOT NewAddToStockItemSale( 0, 0, 0, 0, '', '', '', 0, 0, nNewSubItemNo, SH_cls_Rollback )
.head 7 -  Set bOk = FALSE
.head 6 +  If NOT NewDeleteFromSub( 0, 0, 0, 0, '', SH_cls_Rollback )
.head 7 -  Set bOk = FALSE
.head 6 +  If NOT CheckItemIsOkForCust( 0, 0, 0, bOk, SH_cls_Rollback )
.head 7 -  Set bOk = FALSE
.head 6 -  Return bOk
.head 5 +  Else If IsFlagSet( nActionType, SH_cls_Disconnect )
.head 6 -  Set bOk = TRUE
.head 6 +  If NOT GetOrderBasicDetails( 0, DATETIME_Null, nOldItemNo, nOldSubsItemNo, nOldYear, nOldOrdAmt, nOldConfAmt, sOldAllocFlag, nOldBatchLocId, nOldBatchYear, SH_cls_Disconnect )
.head 7 -  Set bOk = FALSE
.head 6 +  If NOT GetGenericStockItemFlag( 0, sGenericFlag, SH_cls_Disconnect )
.head 7 -  Set bOk = FALSE
.head 6 +  If NOT NewDeductFromStockItemSale( 0, 0, 0, 0, '', '', 0, 0, SH_cls_Disconnect  )
.head 7 -  Set bOk = FALSE
.head 6 +  If NOT NewAddToStockItemSale( 0, 0, 0, 0, '', '', '', 0, 0, nNewSubItemNo, SH_cls_Disconnect )
.head 7 -  Set bOk = FALSE
.head 6 +  If NOT NewDeleteFromSub( 0, 0, 0, 0, '', SH_cls_Disconnect )
.head 7 -  Set bOk = FALSE
.head 6 +  If NOT CheckItemIsOkForCust( 0, 0, 0, bOk, SH_cls_Disconnect )
.head 7 -  Set bOk = FALSE
.head 6 -  Return bOk
.head 3 +  Function: NewSetFlagsOnOrdChange
.head 4 -  Description: Set Ack_Flag and Conf_Flag = 'N' on one order line for customer
to force the reprint of the acknowledgments and confirmations.
.head 4 +  Returns
.head 5 -  Boolean:
.head 4 +  Parameters
.head 5 -  Number: nCustNo
.head 5 -  Number: nYear
.head 5 -  Number: nActionType
.head 4 +  Static Variables
.head 5 -  ! Sql Handle: hSqlSelectHandle
.head 5 -  ! Boolean: bHandleSelectConnected
.head 5 -  ! Boolean: bHandleSelectPrepared
.head 5 -  !
.head 5 -  ! Sql Handle: hSqlUpdHandle
.head 5 -  ! Boolean: bHandleUpdConnected
.head 5 -  ! Boolean: bHandleUpdPrepared
.head 4 +  Local variables
.head 5 -  String: sSql
.head 5 -  String: sBind
.head 5 -  String: sInto
.head 5 -  String: sName
.head 5 -  Boolean: bOk
.head 5 -  Number: nOurSelectHandleNo
.head 5 -  Number: nOurUpdtHandleNo
.head 5 -  Number: nInd
.head 5 -  Date/Time: dtOrderDTStamp
.head 4 +  Actions
.head 5 -  Set nOurSelectHandleNo = SqlHandlesGetReferenceNo( 'NewSetFlagsOnOrdChangeSelect' )
.head 5 -  Set nOurUpdtHandleNo = SqlHandlesGetReferenceNo( 'NewSetFlagsOnOrdChangeUpdt' )
.head 5 +  Select Case nActionType
.head 6 +  Case SH_cls_Execute
.head 7 -  Set sSql = " SELECT Order_Date_Time
FROM Customer_Order 
WHERE Cust_No = :1 AND
  Year_Of_Sale = :nYear AND
  Invoiced_Flag = 'N' AND
  Pull_Sheet_Issued = 'N'  "
.head 7 -  Set sName = 'STFLGSORDCHNGE'
.head 7 -  Set sBind = ':nCustNo'
.head 7 -  Set sInto = ':dtOrderDTStamp'
.head 7 -  Call haSqlHandles[ nOurSelectHandleNo ].Setup( sSql, sName, sBind, sInto )
.head 7 -  Call SqlVarSetup( haSqlHandles[ nOurSelectHandleNo ].hSqlHandle )
.head 7 -  !
.head 7 -  Set sSql = " UPDATE Customer_Order
SET Ack_Flag = 'N', Conf_Flag = 'N'
WHERE Cust_No = :1 AND
  Order_Date_Time = :2 "
.head 7 -  Set sName = 'UPDTORDFLGS'
.head 7 -  Set sBind = ':nCustNo, :dtOrderDTStamp'
.head 7 -  Set sInto = ''
.head 7 -  Call haSqlHandles[ nOurUpdtHandleNo ].Setup( sSql, sName, sBind, sInto )
.head 7 -  Call SqlVarSetup( haSqlHandles[ nOurUpdtHandleNo ].hSqlHandle )
.head 7 -  !
.head 7 -  Set dtOrderDTStamp = DATETIME_Null
.head 7 -  !
.head 7 +  If haSqlHandles[ nOurSelectHandleNo ].Execute( )
.head 8 +  If haSqlHandles[ nOurSelectHandleNo ].FetchNext( nInd )
.head 9 -  Return haSqlHandles[ nOurUpdtHandleNo ].Execute( )
.head 8 +  Else
.head 9 -  Return TRUE
.head 7 +  Else
.head 8 -  Return FALSE
.head 6 +  Case SH_cls_Commit
.head 7 -  Return haSqlHandles[ nOurUpdtHandleNo ].Commit( )
.head 6 +  Case SH_cls_Rollback
.head 7 -  Return haSqlHandles[ nOurUpdtHandleNo ].Rollback( )
.head 6 +  Case SH_cls_Disconnect
.head 7 -  Set bOk = TRUE
.head 7 +  If NOT haSqlHandles[ nOurSelectHandleNo ].Disconnect( )
.head 8 -  Set bOk = FALSE
.head 7 +  If NOT haSqlHandles[ nOurUpdtHandleNo ].Disconnect( )
.head 8 -  Set bOk = FALSE
.head 7 -  Return bOk
.head 3 +  Function: NewSaveOrder
.head 4 -  Description: Save the changes done to an order
BIG NOTE: nActionType These constants are the SH_cls_Execute, SH_cls_Disconnect, nReprepare,
  SH_cls_Commit, SH_cls_Rollback are the values MUST be 2,4,8,16,32,64,128,256 etc and
  nLess20OkDontAsk OR nLess20NotOkDontAsk must also have a value in this sequence.
IF the application does not want the message "Item is less than 20! Continue YES/NO" to
  be asked then OR together SH_cls_Execute | nLess20OkDontAsk OR SH_cls_Execute | nLess20NotOkDontAsk
  to asume a no user interaction action.  By default the message will be asked!
ALSO Assumed is that nLess20OkDontAsk and nLess20NotOkDontAsk will not be used
  together in the one OR statement.
USER nItemCheck Flag ORd onto the SH_cls_Execute to perform checks for item sold out, prohibited
for customer etc.  Can also use nNoMsg flag ORd to stop these message boxes from appearing.
